.)  After doing several things you get a bag from a guy in the pottery shop.  You have to loot no drop bones from skels in the newbie area.  Takes a while, an uncommon spawn with an uncommon drop.   But I got the bones.  Combined em.  Then you combine em with another no drop  item in a bowl you get from the potter guy.   Oops.   Turns out you need pottery skill about 25 to do this.   So start over and get those bones again. Then take a while and get your pottery skill to 30+ because you dont want to miss the second time.  Get the $$%$@!  bones again and combine, make the stuff and .... ouch.  Now you have take the stuff to another bozo.  He gives you ANOTHER bag to fill with rockhopper hides.  Ok, back to the newbie area.  Of course the rockhoppers of the right kind are rarer than the skells so you work for a LONG time and after about 40 kills you have the hides.  You combine, give the bag back to the bozo, and you have the pottery item you made, two items from the bozo and  your initiates cloak (remember that?).<br><br>You go back to the pottery guy and are almost done.<br><br>(Remember this is a newbie quest.)<br><br>You give him the four items and....<br><br>oops.<br><br>You didnt FIRE the pottery item.  So the other three items...<br>disappeared.  Because you see giving the unfired item to the same guy was an earlier step in the quest, so since the item was one given... etc.<br><br>But dont go back and do the rockhoppers again because, YOU IDIOT, you NO LONGER have the initiate's cloak.  And that quest can be done once only.    AND you should feel fortunate that you didnt get your account canceled at once because clearly YOU ARE TOO STUPID to play EQ.<br><br>And I am going to do an epic warrior quest someday!?  Hahahhahaha.<br><br>--- just a tad discouraged tonight.  And I think other guildies have a right to know who they are dealing with LOL.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br> <p>Macbruson 45 barb warBruloff 35 high elf clericBruseco